The `sort()` method sorts the elements of an array in place and returns the array. By default, it compares strings as Unicode code points, which results in a sort that is equivalent to lexicographical comparison but takes into account the numerical values of characters in different scripts (like Arabic or Chinese). If you want to sort the array in ascending order, no additional configuration is needed.

